# 🕷️ Web Scraping Demo

A beginner-friendly Python project that demonstrates how to scrape business listing data (names and locations) from a website using **BeautifulSoup** and **Requests**, then organize the results into a structured **Pandas DataFrame**.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This notebook scrapes similar business listings from a [Yellow Pages India](yellowpages.in/) business page and extracts:
* **Business Names**
* **Business Locations**

The extracted data is then loaded into a Pandas DataFrame for easy viewing and further analysis.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `requests` | Sending HTTP GET requests to fetch webpage HTML |
| `BeautifulSoup` (bs4) | Parsing and navigating the HTML structure |
| `pandas` | Organizing scraped data into a DataFrame |
| `lxml` | HTML parser backend for BeautifulSoup |

